JMPD officers rescue children from window ledge Twitter/@JoburgMPD JOHANNESBURG - A JMPD member has rescued two little girls from the ledge of a building in Johannesburg. The girls aged two and five were seen walking on a ledge on the third floor of a building. WATCH: David Tembe outlines plans to restore dignity of JMPD, EMS Acting sergeant  Tebogo Mailula acted swiftly with the assistance of a member of the public. Mailula, who was on a patrol in the CBD along with three other officers as part of Operation Buya Mthetho, reached the girls from the floor below. The girls' mother had left them sleeping in the flat while she went to the butchery. The MMC for Safety and Security in the City of Johannesburg, Councillor David Tembe, has commended the sergeant for his bravery. Whilst conducting #BuyaMthetho patrol in the JHB CBD #JMPD officers TG Mailula & OG Nkhutlelang came across a group of people at Cnr Bree & End St who stopped them to assists a 2 years & 5 years old girls who had climbed out the window on the 3rd floor of a building.#SaferJoburg pic.twitter.com/1REXI1um9t